HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 102
BY REPRESENTATIVE CARPENTER
A RESOLUTION
To commend Noreen E. Little on the occasion of her election as national president of Phi
Delta Kappa, Incorporated, and to recognize her service, leadership, and
contributions to education.
WHEREAS, Noreen E. Little has dedicated thirty-four years of service to the New
York City Department of Education, where she has served as an early childhood teacher,
assistant principal, and principal of kindergarten through eighth grade; she holds
certifications in elementary education, reading specialist, and school administration and
supervision; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Little has been a committed member of the National Sorority of Phi
Delta Kappa, Incorporated, Eastern Region, Beta Omicron Chapter in Jamaica, New York,
since 1986; she has held numerous chapter offices including basileus, second anti-basileus,
tamiouchos, grammateus, and dean of pledgees; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Little has provided distinguished leadership at the regional level
by serving as kudos chair, tamiouchos, audit chair, and parliamentarian; she served as
elected eastern region director in 2015 and played an instrumental role in reactivating the
Epsilon Sigma Chapter in Gastonia, North Carolina; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Little co-chaired the 2009 Youth Leadership Conference, chaired
the 2024 Eastern Region Conference, and was named a Diamond Life Member in 2019; after
being elected first supreme anti-basileus, she launched the NSPDK, Incorporated, e-Learning
Academy and implemented a town hall series to deliver timely professional content to
members; and
