HR NO. 102 ENROLLED
WHEREAS, Mrs. Little is supported by her husband, Allan, and their three adult
children; her election as national president of the National Sorority of Phi Delta Kappa,
Incorporated, is a testament to her sustained commitment to educational excellence,
organizational service, and the development of youth and professional members.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Noreen E. Little on the occasion of her
election as national president of Phi Delta Kappa, Incorporated; does hereby express
enduring appreciation for her exemplary service, visionary leadership, and contributions to
education; and does hereby encourage the support of her peers for her ongoing work on
behalf of students, educators, and sorority members.
